Day 4 (Daily Problem)
-------------------------------------------------
Question
----------
Burrrrrrrp
Create a function that returns the string "Burp" with the amount of "r's" determined by the input parameters of the function.

Examples
longBurp(3) ? "Burrrp"

longBurp(5) ? "Burrrrrp"

longBurp(9) ? "Burrrrrrrrrp"
Notes
Expect num to always be >= 1.
Remember to use a capital "B".
Don't forget to return the result.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Solution
-----------
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

void longBurp(int p);

int main(){
	int n;
	cout<<"Enter the no. of r's: \n";
	cin>>n;
	longBurp(n);
}

void longBurp(int p){
	cout<<"Bu";
	for(int i=0;i<p;i++){
		cout<<"r";
	}
	cout<<"p"<<endl;
}
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
